batsman = []
matches_played = []
for i in RCB_M.batsman.unique():
    batsman.append(i)
    matches_played.append(len(RCB_M[RCB_M.batsman == i].match_id.unique()))

    
RCB_M_W = RCB_M[RCB_M.player_dismissed != 0].groupby(["batsman"])["player_dismissed"].count().reset_index()

# interactive scatter plot
def create_scatter(feature1, feature2):
    with plt.style.context("ggplot"):
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))

        plt.scatter(x = RCB_M_W[feature1],
                    y = RCB_M_W[feature2],
                    c=RCB_M_W.index,
                    s=300
                   )

        plt.xlabel(feature1.capitalize())
        plt.ylabel(feature2.capitalize())

        plt.title("%s vs %s"%(feature1.capitalize(), feature2.capitalize()))
        plt.show()

feature1_drop = widgets.Dropdown(options=RCB_M_W.columns, value = RCB_M_W.columns[0])
feature2_drop = widgets.Dropdown(options=RCB_M_W.columns, value = RCB_M_W.columns[1])
out = widgets.interactive_output(create_scatter, {'feature1': feature1_drop, 'feature2':feature2_drop})
